Thank you, sir.

825
01:06:51,382 --> 01:06:52,258
Great work.

826
01:06:52,341 --> 01:06:53,592
Thank you for everything.

827
01:06:57,555 --> 01:06:58,431
Thank you, sir.

828
01:06:58,514 --> 01:06:59,765
Thank you.

829
01:07:01,434 --> 01:07:02,560
Thank you, sir.

830
01:07:04,895 --> 01:07:05,813
Good work.

831
01:07:06,105 --> 01:07:07,106
Thank you, sir.

832
01:08:18,094 --> 01:08:19,553
I have something to confess.

833
01:08:19,637 --> 01:08:20,638
Again?

834
01:08:23,891 --> 01:08:25,101
Don't tell me

835
01:08:26,936 --> 01:08:30,439
you were fired from the school.

836
01:08:32,066 --> 01:08:33,234
No, it's not that.

837
01:08:34,068 --> 01:08:36,737
We're on our way to go camping.

838
01:08:37,154 --> 01:08:39,573
But if you suddenly tell me that you need
to confess something,

839
01:08:40,241 --> 01:08:41,867
wouldn't I be startled?

840
01:08:42,827 --> 01:08:45,412
So what is it?

841
01:08:45,913 --> 01:08:48,457
I made sure to bring everything.

842
01:08:48,749 --> 01:08:51,877
I got the burner and equipment
for the campfire and sleeping bags.

843
01:08:51,961 --> 01:08:55,506
I even brought a beam projector
so you and the kids could watch movies.

844
01:08:58,134 --> 01:08:59,802
Mom, I want to watch Frozen.

845
01:09:00,719 --> 01:09:03,931
Aren't you sick of that? Watching it
every day won't turn you into Elsa.

846
01:09:04,181 --> 01:09:05,474
And you look like Olaf.

847
01:09:06,100 --> 01:09:08,185
Mom, Si-wan said--

848
01:09:08,269 --> 01:09:11,397
Si-jin, if you cry right now,
I won't let you watch it.

849
01:09:11,564 --> 01:09:13,107
Si-wan, if you keep teasing her,

850
01:09:13,190 --> 01:09:15,234
I'll deduct 30 minutes
from your game time.

851
01:09:17,361 --> 01:09:18,904
And you, keep talking.

852
01:09:22,491 --> 01:09:23,659
I forgot

853
01:09:24,910 --> 01:09:26,245
the tent.

854
01:09:29,790 --> 01:09:30,624
What?

855
01:09:30,708 --> 01:09:31,542
-Dad!
-Dad!

856
01:09:39,884 --> 01:09:42,136
ANSAN, AUTO CAMPING SITE

857
01:09:51,478 --> 01:09:54,607
Can you take these inside?

858
01:09:55,191 --> 01:09:56,317
Over there.

859
01:09:58,110 --> 01:10:00,362
We could place this here.

860
01:10:04,575 --> 01:10:07,411
They even lent us a tent. It's great.

861
01:10:07,494 --> 01:10:09,038
Next time, we should come empty-handed.

862
01:10:10,414 --> 01:10:11,582
Here.

863
01:10:12,958 --> 01:10:14,835
I think we're done.

864
01:10:16,754 --> 01:10:18,297
Would you like to walk with me?

865
01:10:27,640 --> 01:10:28,599
Hey.

866
01:10:30,226 --> 01:10:31,727
There's something else, right?

867
01:10:34,146 --> 01:10:37,441
How could a meticulous person like you
forget to bring the tent?

868
01:10:39,652 --> 01:10:42,905
There seemed to be something
on your mind these days.

869
01:10:44,031 --> 01:10:47,451
Is that why you wanted to camp
even though you had a big trial next week?

870
01:10:49,745 --> 01:10:53,499
This is how much I care about you.

871
01:10:57,461 --> 01:10:58,587
To be honest,

872
01:11:01,382 --> 01:11:05,010
Stanford University contacted me.
They'd like me to replace Professor Jeong.

873
01:11:06,345 --> 01:11:08,347
They invited me to become a member

874
01:11:08,973 --> 01:11:10,516
of their Air Pollution Society.

875
01:11:12,059 --> 01:11:12,935
Stanford?

876
01:11:15,771 --> 01:11:17,064
What do you want to do?

877
01:11:26,824 --> 01:11:28,242
I heard there's an ocean nearby.

878
01:11:28,325 --> 01:11:30,160
We can't miss it when we came
all the way here.

879
01:11:41,755 --> 01:11:43,090
They're so cute.

880
01:11:49,888 --> 01:11:51,098
This is unexpected of you.

881
01:11:53,392 --> 01:11:54,518
That's the best school

882
01:11:55,394 --> 01:11:56,854
when it comes to Environmentology.

883
01:11:57,771 --> 01:11:59,064
Aren't the conditions quite nice?

884
01:12:01,150 --> 01:12:02,276
What is it?

885
01:12:02,901 --> 01:12:03,944
What's bothering you?

886
01:12:09,950 --> 01:12:10,951
If I go,

887
01:12:11,577 --> 01:12:13,370
I'll be staying there
for at least five years.

888
01:12:14,288 --> 01:12:16,832
How will you manage to work
and take care of them singlehandedly?

889
01:12:22,254 --> 01:12:23,464
Apart from that,

890
01:12:25,090 --> 01:12:27,968
is there anything else
that's holding you back?

891
01:12:41,857 --> 01:12:43,984
It feels great to get some fresh air.

892
01:12:44,818 --> 01:12:46,528
The sunset is beautiful too.

893
01:12:59,750 --> 01:13:01,460
I've heard a lot about you.

894
01:13:01,877 --> 01:13:04,880
I heard you're the best in our country
when it comes to political technology.

895
01:13:06,048 --> 01:13:07,591
Thank you for calling me over.

896
01:13:08,300 --> 01:13:09,635
-Sit down.
-Yes, sir.

897
01:13:09,718 --> 01:13:13,013
I heard that you supported
both the late president Yang Jin-man

898
01:13:13,097 --> 01:13:14,640
and the acting president, Park Mu-jin.

899
01:13:16,266 --> 01:13:17,893
Yes, I did serve them.

900
01:13:19,520 --> 01:13:22,773
Do you have any plans to help me

901
01:13:23,440 --> 01:13:25,901
run for president after two years?

902
01:13:27,069 --> 01:13:29,405
I'm from TK.

903
01:13:29,613 --> 01:13:32,574
I went to school
in South Gyeongsang Province, Busan.

904
01:13:32,658 --> 01:13:34,076
My in-laws are from Honam.

905
01:13:34,159 --> 01:13:38,080
My parents and brothers run a large farm
in Chungcheong Province.

906
01:13:38,163 --> 01:13:39,331
That's great.

907
01:13:39,581 --> 01:13:44,253
My religion is Christianity,
the largest single religion.

908
01:13:44,336 --> 01:13:45,671
My wife is Buddhist.

909
01:13:47,673 --> 01:13:49,133
The majority

910
01:13:50,092 --> 01:13:52,261
of the faction in my party
is supporting me.

911
01:13:52,386 --> 01:13:55,848
Well, I guess you could say
that they're my political assets.

912
01:13:56,473 --> 01:14:01,603
It seems like you've had it easy
up until now.

913
01:14:03,313 --> 01:14:05,190
You've never had to sacrifice anything.

914
01:14:08,527 --> 01:14:10,404
I'm afraid I won't be able
to help you, sir.

915
01:14:12,698 --> 01:14:14,283
Are you disappointed in me?

916
01:14:16,952 --> 01:14:21,623
I seek benefits practicality
more than moral obligations.

917
01:14:21,790 --> 01:14:23,792
It's the 21st century.
Politics ought to change.

918
01:14:25,335 --> 01:14:28,088
You should try calculating
our chances of winning.

919
01:14:28,797 --> 01:14:30,966
In a political technological way, that is.

920
01:14:31,800 --> 01:14:33,177
There is a master key

921
01:14:34,303 --> 01:14:35,471
when it comes to

922
01:14:36,180 --> 01:14:37,431
political technology.

923
01:14:38,891 --> 01:14:40,017
Sacrifice.

924
01:14:40,976 --> 01:14:43,562
The supporters feel like
they owe something to you.

925
01:14:44,521 --> 01:14:47,858
They think,
"We should at least vote for that fool."

926
01:14:48,233 --> 01:14:50,319
It's an investment with a high profit.

927
01:14:51,320 --> 01:14:52,488
In politics,

928
01:14:52,821 --> 01:14:55,365
I think being faithful to a cause is

929
01:14:55,449 --> 01:14:58,243
the most practical and pragmatic choice.

930
01:14:58,327 --> 01:14:59,244
That's why I--

931
01:14:59,328 --> 01:15:00,537
Politically speaking,

932
01:15:01,038 --> 01:15:03,707
you have no chance of winning.

933
01:15:04,750 --> 01:15:06,585
And I don't do losing battles.

934
01:15:08,837 --> 01:15:11,590
Do you have anyone in your mind?

935
01:15:16,220 --> 01:15:18,931
We're gathering signatures for
the enactment of the Discrimination Act.

936
01:15:19,014 --> 01:15:20,015
May I explain briefly?

937
01:15:20,098 --> 01:15:21,517
Could you take a look at this?

938
01:15:21,600 --> 01:15:23,268
I'm good. Later.

939
01:15:24,603 --> 01:15:26,146
Would you like to take a look at this?

940
01:15:26,230 --> 01:15:27,856
-I'm busy.
-Please take a look.

941
01:15:27,940 --> 01:15:29,525
We're gathering signatures.

942
01:15:29,608 --> 01:15:32,319
Everyone, this law
is against any discrimination

943
01:15:32,402 --> 01:15:35,322
based on medical history, appearance,

944
01:15:35,405 --> 01:15:36,907
hometown, and race in Korea.

945
01:15:36,990 --> 01:15:39,451
Your cooperation would be
very much appreciated.

946
01:15:40,244 --> 01:15:43,956
"Signature campaign for
the enactment of the Discrimination Act."

947
01:15:47,125 --> 01:15:49,628
A minority group is campaigning

948
01:15:49,711 --> 01:15:52,172
to make a law for minorities.

949
01:15:52,256 --> 01:15:54,716
You can't make the law like this.

950
01:15:56,176 --> 01:15:58,136
Forget the signatures.

951
01:15:58,220 --> 01:16:00,055
Let's propose a bill.

952
01:16:00,889 --> 01:16:02,474
The Discrimination Act.

953
01:16:05,102 --> 01:16:06,687
In the new Blue House.

954
01:16:13,068 --> 01:16:15,070
Thank you, sir.

955
01:16:15,821 --> 01:16:19,116
Sir, there will be Mr. Wang's
speech about the business strategy

956
01:16:19,199 --> 01:16:20,993
regarding next year's economic growth rate

957
01:16:21,076 --> 01:16:23,745
at the presidential meeting
this afternoon.

958
01:16:23,829 --> 01:16:24,997
The document from yesterday--

959
01:16:29,793 --> 01:16:30,794
Yes, sir.

960
01:16:34,548 --> 01:16:36,508
Mr. Park, do you know

961
01:16:36,592 --> 01:16:38,969
why I keep you despite your high salary?

962
01:16:39,803 --> 01:16:40,762
Pardon, sir?

963
01:16:40,846 --> 01:16:42,848
The Protocol Administrator

964
01:16:42,931 --> 01:16:44,558
serves me as my servant.

965
01:16:44,641 --> 01:16:46,184
What a sight to see, right?

966
01:16:47,769 --> 01:16:50,105
So stop talking

967
01:16:50,439 --> 01:16:52,357
and focus on serving.

968
01:16:57,237 --> 01:16:59,489
Your next appointment is...

969
01:17:05,245 --> 01:17:06,955
Yes, sir. I'll contact him right away.

970
01:17:07,039 --> 01:17:08,040
Sir.

971
01:17:08,123 --> 01:17:09,958
Okay, thank you.

972
01:17:10,042 --> 01:17:11,293
Please take good care of it.

973
01:17:20,135 --> 01:17:21,386
Sir.

974
01:17:22,471 --> 01:17:23,764
This is not a protocol.

975
01:17:28,018 --> 01:17:29,686
This is called a power trip.

976
01:17:31,355 --> 01:17:32,522
And

977
01:17:33,273 --> 01:17:34,274
I don't want

978
01:17:35,525 --> 01:17:37,527
to be your employee

979
01:17:39,613 --> 01:17:40,656
any more.

980
01:17:53,377 --> 01:17:54,378
Let's go.

981
01:17:54,795 --> 01:17:56,338
Before they see me shivering.

982
01:18:03,637 --> 01:18:05,055
A JOURNEY WITH READING, YOUTH

983
01:18:05,138 --> 01:18:06,139
Hi.

984
01:18:06,765 --> 01:18:11,019
Thank you very much
for sitting through the lecture today.

985
01:18:11,812 --> 01:18:13,105
When I was young,

986
01:18:13,438 --> 01:18:16,525
I traveled to over 200 countries

987
01:18:16,650 --> 01:18:18,276
and met people.

988
01:18:18,360 --> 01:18:19,361
Sir.

989
01:18:19,569 --> 01:18:22,614
The number of countries that the current
Korean passport allows you to travel

990
01:18:22,698 --> 01:18:24,533
is 166.

991
01:18:26,660 --> 01:18:30,622
Isn't Ms. Jeong one smart woman?

992
01:18:31,623 --> 01:18:33,417
Please give us a second. Come here.

993
01:18:36,253 --> 01:18:38,213
You just humiliated me
in front of the press.

994
01:18:38,547 --> 01:18:40,382
Are you trying to get attention?

995
01:18:41,425 --> 01:18:42,968
What did you learn in the Blue House?

996
01:18:50,308 --> 01:18:51,768
-Yes, Jeong Su-jeong speaking.
-Hi.

997
01:18:52,269 --> 01:18:54,688
You did great.

998
01:18:55,605 --> 01:18:58,066
-Thank you.
-Okay. I see.

999
01:19:01,695 --> 01:19:03,572
-Could you look over here?
-Sir.

1000
01:19:04,865 --> 01:19:07,075
This is what I learned in the Blue House.

1001
01:19:07,159 --> 01:19:11,079
The most important thing in managing
communication with the people and press

1002
01:19:11,663 --> 01:19:13,081
is honesty and trust.

1003
01:19:14,833 --> 01:19:17,002
Those are the basics in politics.

1004
01:19:27,721 --> 01:19:30,766
Yes, we're at the bus stop
right in front of the entrance.

1005
01:19:31,808 --> 01:19:33,477
Yes. Hey.

1006
01:19:39,524 --> 01:19:40,984
-Have you been waiting long?
-No.

1007
01:19:41,860 --> 01:19:44,446
Let's go. There are people waiting.

1008
01:19:45,322 --> 01:19:46,239
I got you coffee.

1009
01:19:46,364 --> 01:19:49,284
What's going on between the two?
Is something going on or has it happened?

1010
01:19:49,367 --> 01:19:51,995
Why don't you ask them?
It's not like they're strangers.

1011
01:19:52,537 --> 01:19:55,457
I can't ask them
because they're not strangers.

1012
01:19:57,083 --> 01:19:59,628
Long time no see, Mr. Kim Nam-wook.

1013
01:20:01,004 --> 01:20:02,923
Are you two seeing each other? Are you?

1014
01:20:07,469 --> 01:20:08,804
What?

1015
01:20:09,012 --> 01:20:10,013
Yes.

1016
01:20:13,767 --> 01:20:14,684
Have you been well?

1017
01:20:16,353 --> 01:20:18,522
Yes, what about you?

1018
01:20:21,399 --> 01:20:22,651
HEARING ON FINE DUST REDUCTION

1019
01:20:22,734 --> 01:20:24,528
The domestic emissions have a huge impact

1020
01:20:24,611 --> 01:20:25,987
on the fine dust level in Korea

1021
01:20:26,071 --> 01:20:29,533
as well as the emissions outside of Korea.

1022
01:20:29,908 --> 01:20:33,245
It has been already proved
with numerous scientific evidence.

1023
01:20:33,829 --> 01:20:36,122
In order to reduce
the fine dust level in Korea,

1024
01:20:36,206 --> 01:20:38,083
and in order to instigate cooperation

1025
01:20:38,166 --> 01:20:40,877
with our neighboring countries

1026
01:20:40,961 --> 01:20:43,088
for the fine dust reduction,

1027
01:20:43,171 --> 01:20:47,133
we must reduce the cause
of domestic emissions.

1028
01:20:51,680 --> 01:20:54,850
In Korea, there are two major factors
that need to be reduced.

1029
01:20:54,933 --> 01:20:57,310
First, in the metropolitan area,

1030
01:20:57,394 --> 01:20:59,980
the emissions from old diesel vehicles

1031
01:21:00,063 --> 01:21:02,983
are the main cause that increases
the fine dust concentration.

1032
01:21:03,233 --> 01:21:06,778
We must produce fewer diesel vehicles
and develop environment-friendly vehicles

1033
01:21:06,862 --> 01:21:10,323
like electric vehicles, hydrogen vehicles,

1034
01:21:10,407 --> 01:21:12,784
and hybrid vehicles.

1035
01:21:16,121 --> 01:21:20,083
On a national scale, the illegal emissions
from manufactories are the biggest cause.

1036
01:21:20,584 --> 01:21:22,419
We need continuous supervision over them

1037
01:21:22,502 --> 01:21:25,839
to have the corporations
fulfill their environmental responsibility

1038
01:21:25,922 --> 01:21:28,842
and protect people's right to health.

1039
01:21:30,552 --> 01:21:31,761
I have a question.

1040
01:21:39,936 --> 01:21:42,230
I think the calculation is a bit wrong.

1041
01:21:43,982 --> 01:21:45,317
Do you really believe so?

1042
01:22:00,790 --> 01:22:01,625
It's been a while

1043
01:22:01,708 --> 01:22:06,504
since we have seen the blue sky
in spring because of the fine dust.

1044
01:22:07,005 --> 01:22:09,174
Just by turning the diesel vehicles

1045
01:22:09,257 --> 01:22:12,177
into environment-friendly vehicles
and with a couple of reduction policies,

1046
01:22:12,260 --> 01:22:15,221
do you really think
we can reduce the fine dust?

1047
01:22:17,891 --> 01:22:18,975
Do you really believe

1048
01:22:19,184 --> 01:22:20,852
the policies and politics

1049
01:22:21,394 --> 01:22:23,271
can solve the problem?

1050
01:22:24,731 --> 01:22:26,983
If politics can't,

1051
01:22:27,400 --> 01:22:28,610
what else can?

1052
01:22:31,488 --> 01:22:32,864
Politics

1053
01:22:33,281 --> 01:22:36,117
is an endless human endeavor

1054
01:22:36,701 --> 01:22:39,454
to find answers to all the pains
given by the Almighty.

1055
01:22:52,676 --> 01:22:56,096
I heard Stanford University had offered
you an academic position.

1056
01:22:56,805 --> 01:22:58,264
Are you taking the offer?

1057
01:22:58,848 --> 01:23:01,476
I think it'll be of great help
to my fine dust research.

1058
01:23:02,060 --> 01:23:05,146
I thought you just said
politics must solve the fine dust issue.

1059
01:23:07,148 --> 01:23:09,234
You're always against whatever I do.

1060
01:23:10,318 --> 01:23:11,528
You haven't changed, Mr. Cha.

1061
01:23:11,611 --> 01:23:13,530
Some things have changed.

1062
01:23:16,032 --> 01:23:19,703
Usually, I don't make
more than three offers.

1063
01:23:21,705 --> 01:23:23,832
But you're an exception.

1064
01:23:26,835 --> 01:23:29,838
Would you run
for the next presidential election?

1065
01:23:31,464 --> 01:23:32,507
We...

1066
01:23:33,967 --> 01:23:35,176
will be with you.

1067
01:23:39,556 --> 01:23:41,057
I would like to see it too.

1068
01:23:43,059 --> 01:23:45,603
A world where good people win. Wait, no.

1069
01:23:46,521 --> 01:23:49,149
A world where people win
because they are good.

1070
01:23:53,528 --> 01:23:55,238
I want to be

1071
01:23:55,697 --> 01:23:57,574
with a man who deserves

1072
01:23:58,408 --> 01:23:59,492
my service.

1073
01:24:02,787 --> 01:24:03,788
Could you

1074
01:24:05,999 --> 01:24:07,167
give us your answer?

1075
01:25:15,401 --> 01:25:22,408
THANK YOU FOR WATCHING
DESIGNATED SURVIVOR: 60 DAYS

